node.text: Welcome to occlusion training with @rossedgley By restricting blood flow and oxygen the muscles are forced to work harder in a shorter period of time and a bunch of other “sports sciency” stuff happens. Basically it’s one of the most uncomfortable training methods I’ve experienced but part of the puzzle in growing Thor’s arms to look like the legs of a racehorse . Don’t try this at home unless you have yourself a professional pain guru like Ross @centrfit #thorloveandthunder

node.text: Bid on these amazing art projects curated by @dansultanmusic from two leading and incredible artists Yuin Monero and wandandian women @niahmcleod and bundajlung man @otiscarey . All in support of @childrensground and the amazing work they do. “CHILDREN’S GROUND IS AN ORGANISATION LED BY ABORIGINAL COMMUNITIES. WE ARE CREATING A NEW FUTURE FOR CHILDREN FILLED WITH PROMISE, HOPE AND EMPOWERMENT”

node.text: Those living with EB can teach us lessons in humility, grace, and bravery. It was an honor to get to know John Hudson and be a part of the #VentureintoCures Virtual Event last night. The world will be a better place when we #HealEB. I encourage you to donate and learn more about @ebresearch by going to ebresearch.org. This video was animated by @davefranciosaart & directed by @mattfinlin of Doorknocker Media. @eddievedder

node.text:
For the first time in 3000 years the Tasmania devils are back on mainland Australia! As top predators, the devils push back feral cats and foxes, allowing Australia’s native small mammals to recover so they can get to work enriching soil as they forage and help forests regenerate. My family and I were lucky enough to be there and lend a hand with the wonderful team at @wild.ark @aussieark @global_wildlife_conservation and #DevilComeback #ReWildAustralia
Head to devilcomeback.org to support!
Shot by visionary, genius ,majestic, Spaniard @cristianprieto.filmmaker

node.text: It was great to spend some time with #swissewellness and @the_malloys earlier this year talking about what it means to live a healthier, happier life. We discussed how training mindfully, eating well, and finding balance in good sleep and recovery have all had a snowball effect on other areas of my life.

node.text:
Gearing up for @netflix Extraction sequel. Transitioning from heavy weight training to a lot more body weight functional movements concentrating on agility, strength and speed. 
Give this little work out a go and let the lungs scream for mercy! @centrfit 💪🤙

3 minute boxing round (cardio)
50 squats (lower body)
40 sit thrus (mobility)
20 reps for each (core)exercise 
25 push ups (upper body) 
Rest 2 minutes  4 sets in total

node.text:
In 2019 I partnered with @Emirates and @EXPO2020Dubai, to help bring awareness to what is a really important event for the world. We all have the power to build a better world and shape the future, and the last year and a half has shown us that the possibilities are endless when we put our minds together. At Expo 2020 Dubai, the world will come together to provide real life solutions to help preserve our planet for future generations. If you are able to travel and you feel it’s safe, I sincerely hope you can make it.

#FlyEmiratesFlyBetter #Expo2020

node.text: Welcome to occlusion training with @rossedgley By restricting blood flow and oxygen the muscles are forced to work harder in a shorter period of time and a bunch of other “sports sciency” stuff happens. Basically it’s one of the most uncomfortable training methods I’ve experienced but part of the puzzle in growing Thor’s arms to look like the legs of a racehorse . Don’t try this at home unless you have yourself a professional pain guru like Ross @centrfit #thorloveandthunder

Reminiscing about good times @thredboresort, had an epic few days at the snow before lockdown. So lucky to have these places in our backyard, @australia. When you can travel again, make sure you get out and support those communities who rely on tourism and are having a particularly tough time. #seeaustralia
